<br>
I'm not in the lucky situation to be able to play a lot of hours without a break.<br>
<br>
How does my normal EQ day look like?<br>
Getting online:<br>
- Summoning some food and water.<br>
- Summoning focus items<br>
- getting Pet<br>
- summoning weapons for Pet<br>
- medding<br>
- buffing myself and Pet<br>
- medding<br>
<br>
Now I think there went the first 10-15 minutes.<br>
Then I have maybe 1 hour or 1.5 hours left to play, if I'm very lucky 2 hours.<br>
<br>
That's hardly enough time to get anywhere as a Mage.<br>
If I want to travel to anywhere I usually spend one playing turn only for travelling.<br>
<br>
It may sound stupid of me, but I just don't want to go to the Temple just to find out about the quest, because that would mean 2 hours of no playing at all.<br>
(And I'm sorry, &quot;playing&quot; for me means hunting something....)<br>
<br>
Sure maybe the Mage is the wrong class for me, but that as my first choice and theoretically I like it. So I need to live with my handicap somehow.<br>
I don't know, maybe I will one day switch completely to my Druid who is currently lvl 21. But that wouldnt be the class I prefer to play ;-)<br>
<br>
I don't know how many time you can (or could in the past) play the game.<br>
But there are people who have a job, who need to sleep a bit but still want to &quot;play&quot; EQ as far as it's possible.<br>
I don't know if you would like to &quot;waste&quot; your precious playing time by just getting from A to B just to get told something by a NPC what you also could find out by asking other players. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ueuphorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Euphorion</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#333333>(4/17/02 9:35:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=932.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: question about focus items</span><hr size=1> Oh, let me be a bit sarcastic now too.... ;-)<br>
<br>
Do or did you ever use printed maps to find your way around?<br>
<br>
If you did never use a map: I truly admire you.<br>
<br>
But if you do or did, think about how much you could have learn and how much enjoyment you'd have gotten from learning about all the different areas without any &quot;non-roleplaying-help&quot;. Because what is the difference between me asking for some quest details and using a player-made-map which helps you not having to learn how to get through the different areas on your own. <br>
<br>
I don't want to use 2 hours to run to some NPC to get some basic quest information and I bet you don't want to run 2 hours through a new zone just to get the basic idea of what is where in the zone.<br>
<br>
Do my attempts to get some information in advance make me a worse player? Maybe.<br>
Do I prefer &quot;cheating&quot; (because if you see it from a roleplaying viewpoint, everything that doesn't come with the game is some kind of &quot;cheating&quot;, because it wouldn't be available to your character in &quot;real Everquest&quot; ) in order to use my available playing time as effectively and enjoyable? definately yes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ueuphorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Euphorion</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#333333>(4/17/02 9:57:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=932.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: question about focus items</span><hr size=1> Grummel....many adds, but I want to say even a bit more.<br>
<br>
I'm not a poor guy (not rich either, but I get along).<br>
So I could have gone to Ebay and could have bought some lvl 50+ account with a ton pp and all that stuff.<br>
<br>
I could have bragged all the time what great equipment I have, how great I am by reaching such a high level and so on.<br>
<br>
And probably I would enjoy EQ a bit more, because I simply could go out and have fun. I wouldn't have to care about how I can afford or get some cheapish stuff in the time that is available.<br>
After I would have learned a bit about the class I could have simply killed things without caring much about anything else.<br>
<br>
Just a few things that happened to me:<br>
A lvl 47 Mage on a horse stood close to where I was fighting when I was around lvl 10.<br>
I greeted him and asked him if I could maybe get a DS and a summoned weapon for my Pet (couldnt afford such summon spells and thoiught a better weapon wouldbe nice).<br>
&quot;What's DS....?&quot;<br>
&quot;Damage shield&quot;<br>
&quot;Hmmm, I don't know if I have a spell called &quot;Damage Shield&quot; &quot;<br>
<br>
At that point he ride away on his nice horse.<br>
Did he get the level by himself and all the stuff by spending thousands of hours? Yeah, probably.<br>
<br>
Or when I played as a lvl 20 Mage in LOIO and I happened to have a lvl 27 druid in my group.<br>
He looked cool in his wolf form and the stuff he did wear looked pretty expensive.<br>
The next half hour I tried to explain him the concept of snaring a MOB and how helpful it often is if the MOB doesn't run away...<br>
A lvl 27 Druid who never heard about &quot;Snare&quot; before?<br>
Did he get the level by himself? Yeah, probably.<br>
Was he &quot;just&quot; powerlevelled? Yeah, probably.<br>
A lvl 20 Mage (and that was my only char at that time) knew about Snaring and so I guess everybody does who was in some groups with ANY char before.<br>
<br>
Why do I write all that stuff?<br>
No idea, probably I just should have taken the comments.<br>
<br>
It just makes me a bit sick if people assume always that everybody can play EQ for the whole day. That they laugh at you, just because they level 3 times as fast as you. That people who are lvl 50 are welcomed in many guilds even if they just bought the char or got it from somewhere else.<br>
That people tell you &quot;You should realy get that and that item.&quot; And when you look what that item is you see that it drops from some lvl 50+ MOB. &quot;Oh, nice, thanks for the advice....&quot;<br>
<br>
But you, as a lowish Mage who tries to get along somehow you are more or less an &quot;outcast&quot; ;-)<br>
<br>
<br>
Am I frustrated? sometimes.<br>
Will I live with my handicap? Have to.<br>
