<br>
When I first made Mantria I had not a clue about playing a mage, much less playing one on Odus.  I spent my first 4 hours wandering the erudite starting city and marveling at the beauty of it all. The game graphics at that time pale to what they are now but I was like a kid in a candy shop. I'd be like ooo ahhh wow look at that or this.  I began to think, hmmm maybe I need to find Tox and try to get some exp(mantria was my 3rd char(others I got to 15th) and I knew some of the basic things).  So I spent almost an hour trying to figure out how to get to the zone. Then finally asked a passing Wizard how I got there. He chuckled, I turned red, and he said come with me. He then showed my the teleport gems and how to use them and how to get to Tox.  Once out in tox I thanked him and started to marvel yet once again. Here was this green forrest with HUGE trees, so high I could not see the tops. (ever seen those pictures of the tourists in big cities staring at the tops of the skyscrappers? that was me)<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
So here I am in Tox looking for stuff to kill. I know about sticking close to the guards so I try not to wander to far.  As anyone who has played an Erudite and tries the newbie area there is like almost ZIP to kill. It took me another 3 hours to level to 3.  As I'm sitting at the guard the same wizard wanders by and asks how its going. I said GREAT I'm level 3 already!!!!  He chuckles once again, I turn red(feeling all the time I'm a tomato) and says would I like to go to a better place then Tox for exp at my level.  I think for a minute and say SURE!(knowing this means I get to see more of the world). He brings me back in Erudin and to the docks. We take a boat to Qeynos(ok NOW I'm really wideeyed and stareing like a kid in a candy shop. Everything is so alive and beautiful!  He says let's wander the city a little and he starts to show me around. Finally we get to the Wizard/Mage/Enchanter guild area and he asks me if I have enough money to buy my 4th level spells. I said I had like 4sp 17cp. He stifles a chuckle(least I hope he did)<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   And tells me to wait near the bank. He is gone for 5mins and then reappears.  Hands me 2 bags, each filled with all my level 1 and level 4 spells. I was so happy.  He then said ok Let's go to Halas(erm what's halas?) He says it'll be my home for the next few weeks.  We start running. In North Qeynos he stops and asks a friendly druid to cast sow on us.  We get to blackborrow and I start con'ing stuff. I'm like this is all red to me and wants my heart on a silver plate. He's like. Not to worry just follow me.  We get through BB and enter Everfrost. Sufice it to say I was in awe.  This place was so beautiful. I'm from a cold climate area so the snow made me feel at home. We start running the canyons. After 10mins He says, Durn I always make that mistake. Huh? Wrong turn<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   We finally get to Halas ramps and zone into Halas. Take the raft across the pond and he binds me near the bank. He shows me around Halas some, shows me the girl to turn in the bear pelts for armor.  Takes me around and then back to the docks. We take the raft back across and zone to Everfrost.  He then explains to me that I need to learn this place, great exp and loot.  He showed me a few tricks like stand back in the canyon near the guards and use burst of flame to bring them to me.  Was a blast. I had help from a friendly player who took pity on me when I was level 3.  <br>
I lived in Everfrost for 20 levels.  I didn't even know about focus items for mages. I didn't know much back then.  Heck I still don't know much, know more but *shrug*. <br>
Point being you can come here, learn everything you can, go back into the game and walk through your gaming life in leaps and bounds.  Will you enjoy it? Porbably because some, as was mentioned, don't have the time to explore the world to its fullest.  I personally wanted to explore the world and see what was out there. I didn't know you could get maps from websites back then(may 2000) Yes I learned zones without maps for the longest time.  Course I never went to many places at first. But still had a blast. <br>
I guess want I'm asking from most is to atleast TRY to help yourself some before anything else.  The one that shows they are trying to learn, are working on their own for whatever reason, willing to ask simple questions will get more respect and help from the high levels then the one who says. Can you hand hold me through life?<br>
<br>
Sorry this got alot longer then I had planed. Take Care and if you ever on Povar look me up I'll help with what I can.<br>
